final_thought: If I plant enough milkweed, if the rains come at the right time, if
  the chemicals stay away from just this one patch... maybe one orange wing will find
  its way home.
last_days_scenario: Elena walks the same mountain paths her great-grandmother showed
  her, but the sacred oyamel groves where billions of monarchs once clustered are
  stumps and cattle pasture. She carries a leather pouch of milkweed seeds, trying
  to replant corridors, but the herbicide spray from adjacent soy fields kills each
  new patch within months. Her teenage daughter refuses to learn the traditional butterfly
  calendar - "Why memorize something that doesn't exist anymore, mamá?" The climate
  research station her family helped run for 30 years closed last spring. Elena still
  wakes at 4 AM to check butterfly traps that haven't caught a monarch in three years.
